{
  "texts": [
    "Here it is also worth highlighting that, if motor effects (such as reaction time) were stable within-subjects but varied between subjects, this would not influence precision estimates because the temporal relationship between systoles and taps would still be clear.",
    "However, the novelty of our approach entails that it should be replicated in future studies.",
    "Another limitation is that, while we did compare models with vs. without learning, we did not compare our model to other existing approaches.",
    "The heartbeat tapping task was not wellsuited for several alternatives we considered.",
    "For example, it did not have a sufficient number of trials to be suited for traditional signal detection approaches, which would be most comparable to our model-based precision measure [107]."
  ]
}